---
/*
  WikiSure™ Demo — Phase 3 (Content Upgrade)
  - No new files
  - No new JS logic
  - Only copy refinement (safe)
*/
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>WikiSure™ Demo</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

    <style>
      :root {
        --blue: #0a3cff;
        --text: #0b1220;
        --muted: #6b7280;
        --border: #e5e7eb;
        --bg: #ffffff;
      }

      * { box-sizing: border-box; }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family:
          -apple-system,
          BlinkMacSystemFont,
          "Segoe UI",
          Roboto,
          Helvetica,
          Arial,
          sans-serif;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      }

      header {
        padding: 18px 28px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
      }

      header a {
        text-decoration: none;
        color: var(--blue);
        font-weight: 500;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      main {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 56px 24px 72px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 30px;
        line-height: 1.25;
        margin: 0 0 16px;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }

      p {
        font-size: 17px;
        line-height: 1.65;
        color: var(--muted);
        margin: 0 0 16px;
      }

      .hint {
        margin-top: 18px;
        padding: 12px 14px;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 12px;
        background: #fafafa;
        color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 14px;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }

      .step { display: none; animation: fadeIn 0.25s ease-out; }
      .step.active { display: block; }

      @keyframes fadeIn {
        from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(4px); }
        to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
      }

      .nav {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        margin-top: 48px;
        gap: 12px;
      }

      button {
        appearance: none;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        background: white;
        padding: 12px 18px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        font-size: 15px;
        font-weight: 500;
        cursor: pointer;
        transition: all 0.15s ease;
      }

      button.primary {
        background: var(--blue);
        color: white;
        border-color: var(--blue);
      }

      button:hover:not(:disabled) { transform: translateY(-1px); }
      button:disabled { opacity: 0.4; cursor: default; }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <header>
      <a href="https://synsuretech.org" target="_blank">← Back to SynsureTech</a>
    </header>

    <main>
      <!-- STEP 1 -->
      <section class="step active" data-step="0">
        <h1>Clarity that accelerates execution</h1>
        <p>
          In partner ecosystems, speed comes from alignment.
          When teams use the same words but interpret them differently,
          delivery slows down and responsibilities blur.
        </p>
        <p>
          WikiSure™ makes key terms explicit and shared —
          so work moves forward with confidence.
        </p>
        <div class="hint">
          This demo is a guided, single-user walkthrough: 6 steps, one governed decision.
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- STEP 2 -->
      <section class="step" data-step="1">
        <h1>One term, multiple partners</h1>
        <p>
          A platform provider coordinates insurers, OEMs, distributors and service partners.
          Small definition gaps create big downstream costs.
        </p>
        <p>
          Here we focus on one term — and show how it becomes implementation-ready.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- STEP 3 -->
      <section class="step" data-step="2">
        <h1>Select the term</h1>
        <p>
          Choose a term that appears across partners, documents and interfaces.
          The goal is not a perfect text — the goal is a shared understanding that holds in practice.
        </p>
        <p>
          Example terms: consent, eligibility, activation, cancellation, coverage start.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- STEP 4 -->
      <section class="step" data-step="3">
        <h1>Make it implementation-ready</h1>
        <p>
          A definition is governed only if two teams can implement the same behavior from it.
          WikiSure™ helps turn fuzzy wording into clear expectations:
          what it means, what it triggers, and who owns what.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outcome: fewer back-and-forth loops and faster, cleaner delivery.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- STEP 5 -->
      <section class="step" data-step="4">
        <h1>Human-in-the-loop decision</h1>
        <p>
          The system can assist with checks and guidance —
          but accountability stays with a person.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is the moment where teams align, document the reasoning,
          and remove ambiguity before it becomes an expensive issue later.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- STEP 6 -->
      <section class="step" data-step="5">
        <h1>A reusable, documented outcome</h1>
        <p>
          The result is not just “yes/no”.
          It’s a decision with context: what was agreed, why, and what happens next.
        </p>
        <p>
          That makes collaboration repeatable — across partners, products and future rollouts.
        </p>
        <div class="hint">
          Next step after this demo: move from single-user to partner validation and traceable versioning.
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="nav">
        <button id="prev" disabled>Back</button>
        <button id="next" class="primary">Next</button>
      </div>
    </main>

    <script>
      const steps = document.querySelectorAll(".step");
      const nextBtn = document.getElementById("next");
      const prevBtn = document.getElementById("prev");

      let current = 0;

      function render() {
        steps.forEach((s, i) => s.classList.toggle("active", i === current));
        prevBtn.disabled = current === 0;
        nextBtn.textContent = current === steps.length - 1 ? "Done" : "Next";
      }

      nextBtn.onclick = () => {
        if (current < steps.length - 1) {
          current++;
          render();
        }
      };

      prevBtn.onclick = () => {
        if (current > 0) {
          current--;
          render();
        }
      };

      render();
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
